description:
&lt;p&gt;North Middlesex University Hospital is a busy District General Hospital based in Edmonton, North London. We have a busy paediatrics service that also offers multiple sub-speciality in patient and out patient care. We have a dedicate paediatric emergency department that currently sees almost 50,000 children a year. We would be keen to appoint a substantive consultant to cover paediatrics/neonates along with interests in Haematology-Oncology. The successful candidate will also take on the role of Deputy Lead for the Paediatric Haem-Onc&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a reputation for excellent training, motivated junior doctors and consistently high quality nursing and allied health professionals. We are compliant with the London Quality standards. We work within a multi-ethnic population with a high index of deprivation. This is both a challenging and a fascinating hospital to work in. We have a reputation as a close knit and friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want to appoint dynamic and enthusiastic consultant. We are looking for an individual who will be passionate about the quality of care they provide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Dr. Dhruv Rastogi (Clinicial Director) on 020 8887 3807 or d.rastogi@nhs.net or Dr Justin Daniels (Divisional Director) on 020 8887 2945, Justin.daniels@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is an Equal Opportunities Employer. We provide a smoke free work environment. Due to the nature of this post, an enhanced Disclosure &amp; Barring Service search will be conducted on the successful applicant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Emma DevereuxJob titleClinical Director - PaediatricsEmail addressemma.devereux@nhs.netTelephone number020 8887 3807Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We encourage informal visits and telephone conversations prior to applying for the roles.&lt;/p&gt;
